  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Sample environment:\r\nDC\r\n   Cluster [zone-a] (Cluster)\r\n      Host1 (Host)\r\n         DS1 (Datastore)\r\n      Host2\r\n         DS2\r\n      Host3\r\n         DS3\r\n\r\nWith a node running under each host, PVC is created with StorageClass having allowedTopologies=zone-a.\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe volume creation might succeed on one of the datastores.\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe volume creation should have actually failed since there is no shared datastore among the hosts in the zone.\r\nThis is because of a bug in datastore intersection logic here:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/59f0f2d2f9cf24564895a80a7640260a6ff27602/staging/src/k8s.io/legacy-cloud-providers/vsphere/vsphere_util.go#L305\r\n\t\t\tif len(sharedDatastoresPerZone) == 0 {\r\n\t\t\t\tsharedDatastoresPerZone = dsObjList\r\n\t\t\t} else {\r\n\t\t\t\tsharedDatastoresPerZone = intersect(sharedDatastoresPerZone, dsObjList)\r\n\t\t\t}\r\nThe code should bail out if sharedDatastoresPerZone is empty in the else block rather than proceeding with the next host/datastore which could cause it to be selected incorrectly. The same fix is applicable when intersecting across zones.\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nAs explained earlier.\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nThis issue will be observed only when allowedTopologies is specified.\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):all\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:vsphere",
